\label{fig:ragale_enforcer}
\end{figure}

% -------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{End-to-End Evaluation}
\label{sec:evaluation}
% -------------------------------------------------------------------------

We evaluate the symbolic enforcer end-to-end on both metres
(\textit{dvipada}, \textit{utsaha ragale}) by running every combination of
two models and three decoding strategies, for a total of twelve benchmark
configurations.

\paragraph{Setup.}
For each language we test the base instruction-tuned model
(\texttt{google/gemma-3-1b-it}) and its LoRA fine-tuned variant
(merged for Telugu, adapter for Kannada; full hyperparameters in
Section~\ref{sec:training_setup}, Table~\ref{tab:training-config}) under
the three decoding strategies introduced in
Section~\ref{sec:constrained}: rejection-free \textit{masking only},
\textit{masking with checkpoint backtracking}, and the \textit{hybrid}
mask + NFA rejection sampler. Each (model, method) cell
generates 102 poems from 3 prompts $\times$ 34 seeds (seeds $42 + 7k$ for
$k\in[0,33]$), giving \textbf{1{,}224 total generations} across the matrix.
Sampling uses temperature $\tau=0.7$, top-$p=0.9$, and \texttt{max\_new\_tokens}
$=150$. All runs use a single NVIDIA RTX~5050 laptop GPU with bfloat16
weights (no quantisation).

\paragraph{Prompts.}
Telugu prompts are mythological/devotional themes drawn from the corpus
(``\textit{tallI prEma annintikaMTe goppadi}'',
``\textit{hanumaMtuDu samudramunu dATi laMkanu cErenu}'',
``\textit{SrIrAmuDu sItAdEvini rakshiMcuTaku laMkaku veLLenu}''). Kannada
prompts are short topical themes (\textit{Bubbles}, \textit{Moon},
\textit{Rain}) instantiated against the prompt templates of
Section~\ref{sec:constrained}: a Kannada-system prompt for the base model
and an English instruction-tuning template that matches the LoRA training
format.

\paragraph{Metrics.}
We report (i) \textit{poem accuracy}, the fraction of generations whose
\emph{both} lines pass the FST+NFA validator; (ii) \textit{line accuracy},
the fraction of individual lines that pass; (iii) average wall time per
poem; (iv) average tokens generated; and (v) average backtrack count.
Validation uses the same chandas pipeline that filtered the training corpus
in Section~\ref{sec:validation}, so generation and dataset construction are
scored against an identical specification.

\paragraph{Reproducibility.}
All twelve benchmark scripts and the corresponding result JSON files are
distributed under \texttt{domino/} (Telugu) and
\texttt{ragale\_pipeline/}\allowbreak\texttt{ragale\_}\allowbreak\texttt{inference\_}\allowbreak\texttt{scripts/}
(Kannada) in the project repository.

% -------------------------------------------------------------------------
\section{Results}
\label{sec:results}
% -------------------------------------------------------------------------

Tables~\ref{tab:dvipada-results} and~\ref{tab:ragale-results} report
poem-level accuracy for the twelve configurations. Per-topic breakdowns and
efficiency statistics are deferred to
Appendix~\ref{app:detailed_results}.

